failing to complete and pass registered hours may make you ineligible for financial aid. You must meet Satisfactory Academic Progress (SAP) requirements to maintain eligibility for financial aid as defined by the UNT Office of Student Financial Aid and Scholarships. See more information on UNT's SAP policies. In addition, if you drop below half-time enrollment you may be required to begin paying back your student loans. Please contact financial aid directly as your situation may vary. Description: For students who have registered and completed fee payment. At this time, students may change their schedules. Payment Deadline: Payment deadline for additional tuition and fees resulting from add/drop is 5:00 p.m., September 1. Add/Drop Schedule Date Details 7:00 a.m., August 25 Add/Drop Allowed 5:30 p.m. - 11:59 p.m., August 30 Registration access is temporarily unavailable due to mandatory processing. 12:00 a.m., August 31 Add/Drop reopens 4:30 p.m., September 1 Last day to add a class 11:59 p.m., September 11 Last day to drop a class online. After this date a student who wishes to drop a course must first receive written consent of the instructor. See important information about dropping classes or withdrawing from the university. Fee Payment Fee payment deadline is 5:00 p.m., September 1 for registration that has occurred as of 4:30 p.m., September 1. Bills will not be mailed for the Fall semester. Go to the Student Center online at my.unt.edu for your account balance and schedule information. Account balance information will be available at my.unt.edu once you complete registration. Go to the myUNT Student Center to view your bill. Fee payment arrangements must be completed by the deadlines stated above, or your registration requests will be canceled and you will not be registered. For information about making payments, please visit studentaccounting.unt.edu. For information about Financial Aid and Scholarships, visit financialaid.unt.edu. Additional Resources For more information, contact the Registrar's Information Counter by calling 940-565-2378 or visiting Eagle Student Services Center (ESSC) Room 147. For instructions on using the myUNT Student Center for Registration, please visit Student Center Help.   Registration Info Find Classes Get Advised   Registration GuidesSpring 2017 Summer 2017 Fall 2017 Academic Catalog View All Forms Instructions for using MyUNT and EIS   Contact Information: Office of the Registrar 1155 Union Circle #311400 Denton, TX 76203-1400 USA Voice: 940-565-2111 Visit Us: Eagle Student Services Building http://registrar.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions on content or technical issues? Please contact us. registrar@unt.edu UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on: April 19, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness 